---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const siteOrigin = (Astro.site ?? new URL('https://jonathanabraham.dev')).toString().replace(/\/$/, '');
const personId = `${siteOrigin}/#jonathan`;
const url = `${siteOrigin}/about`;

const profileJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ProfilePage',
  '@id': `${url}#profile`,
  url,
  name: 'About Jonathan Abraham',
  inLanguage: 'en',
  mainEntity: { '@id': personId },
  about: { '@id': personId },
};

const description = 'Jonathan Abraham — building production AI for over 2 years. Voice agents, intake automation, and backend infrastructure for environments with real users, regulatory requirements, and uptime expectations. Founder of Brokerloop (Melbourne).';
---
<Base
  title="About — Jonathan Abraham"
  description={description}
  pageType="profile"
  jsonLd={profileJsonLd}
>
  <main id="content" class="wrap">
    <header class="page-head">
      <div class="prompt">&gt; ./about</div>
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <figure class="avatar" aria-hidden="false">
        <img src="/about/avatar.jpeg" alt="Jonathan Abraham" width="200" height="200" loading="eager" />
      </figure>

      <p>I'm Jonathan. I've been building production AI for over 2 years — voice agents, intake automation, and the backend infrastructure that keeps AI systems reliable in production. I run <a href="#">Brokerloop</a>, an Australian insurtech, where that work shows up as voice intake, long-form workflows, and Go-based backend systems brokers depend on day to day.</p>

      <p>I came up through full-stack engineering and consulting, which is a less common path into AI than the research route. It means I think about commercial constraints first — pricing, scope, operational reliability, and the work needed to keep a system dependable in production — and treat the model as one component of a working system rather than the point of it.</p>

      <p>This site is mostly working notes — things I've learned shipping production voice AI, building backend infrastructure in Go, and operating an insurtech where compliance, latency, and real customers all have to be handled at once.</p>

      <p>Outside Brokerloop I take on a small number of engagements each year, focused on voice AI and backend AI infrastructure for teams moving from a working prototype to a system that holds up in production. <strong>New work is by referral</strong>. The easiest way to start a conversation is <a href="mailto:jabrahamtech@gmail.com">email</a>.</p>

      <h2>Selected work</h2>
      <ul class="work-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Fraud detection AI · tier-one Australian bank.</strong>
          Architected an AI fraud-detection system for an internal, regulated environment. Confidential client. Constraints in scope: enterprise-grade reliability, regulatory and compliance review, and integration into existing banking infrastructure.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Brokerloop · founder.</strong>
          Voice intake agents and Go-based backend systems for Australian insurance brokers. Production voice handling real callers, long-form intake workflows, and integrations with the platforms brokers depend on day to day.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Low-latency event-driven architecture.</strong>
          Sub-second decision pipeline originally built for prediction markets, generalised to any domain where speed-to-action is the constraint — trading signals, real-time risk, market-making, telemetry-triggered automation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open source · interests.</strong>
          Active interest in <a href="https://github.com/nautechsystems/nautilus_trader" rel="noopener">nautilus_trader</a> (Rust-native trading engine), <a href="https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI" rel="noopener">ComfyUI</a> (diffusion model graph), and <a href="https://github.com/open-webui/open-webui" rel="noopener">open-webui</a> (local LLM tooling).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>runtime:</strong> go · typescript · python · postgres · redis</li>
        <li><strong>ai:</strong> openai · anthropic · groq</li>
        <li><strong>voice:</strong> twilio · deepgram · pipecat · elevenlabs</li>
        <li><strong>ops:</strong> fly.io · cloudflare · supabase · sentry</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>email</strong> — <a href="mailto:jabrahamtech@gmail.com">jabrahamtech@gmail.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>github</strong> — <a href="https://github.com/jabrahamtech" rel="me">/jabrahamtech</a></li>
        <li><strong>linkedin</strong> — <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jabrahamtech" rel="me">/in/jabrahamtech</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <div class="ascii-div" aria-hidden="true">━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━</div>
  </main>
</Base>
